  "text": "The expression of several genes involved in muscle organ development was changed in the current study. MEF2c and NR2F2 are well characterized to be essential for myoblast differentiation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , whereas, Gli1 blocks myoblast differentiation by inhibiting MyoD activation in skeletal muscle [CITATION_3] . In the current study, the increased expression of MEF2c and NR2F2 and a decreased expression of Gli1 at d 30 suggested that feeding pigs with a linseed-enriched diet might increase the differentiation of myogenic cells in porcine skeletal muscle. However, further studies are needed to confirm these results.",
